We need to get data using pandas datareader. We will get stock information for the following banks:

  • Bank of America
  • CitiGroup
  • Goldman Sachs
  • JPMorgan Chase
  • Morgan Stanley
  • Wells Fargo

    From Jan 1st 2006 to Jan 1st 2023 for each of these banks

EDA¶

What is the max Close price for each bank's stock throughout the time period?

In [11]:
bank_stocks.xs(key='Close', axis=1, level='Stock Info').max()
Out[11]:
Bank Ticker
BAC     54.900002
C      564.099976
GS     423.850006
JPM    171.779999
MS     108.730003
WFC     65.930000
dtype: float64

Create a new empty DataFrame called returns. This dataframe will contain the returns for each bank's stock. returns are typically defined by:

$$r_t = \frac{p_t - p_{t-1}}{p_{t-1}} = \frac{p_t}{p_{t-1}} - 1$$
In [12]:
returns = pd.DataFrame()

We can use pandas pct_change() method on the Close column to create a column representing this return value. Creating a for loop that goes and for each Bank Stock Ticker creates this returns column and set's it as a column in the returns DataFrame.

In [13]:
for tick in tickers:
    returns[tick+' Return']= bank_stocks[tick]['Close'].pct_change()
returns.head()

We notice that 4 banks had the worst return on '2009-01-20'and that day was the day that Barak Obama was inaugurated as the president of The United States

What Stocks are the riskiest? and what is the safest?

In [18]:
returns.std().sort_values()
Out[18]:
GS Return     0.023078
JPM Return    0.024309
WFC Return    0.026867
BAC Return    0.031171
MS Return     0.031985
C Return      0.032954
dtype: float64

CitiGroup has the highest standard deviation so it is the riskiest,
and Goldman Sachs has the lowest standard deviation with the lowest risk

What was the safest stock during 2022?

Moving Averages¶

Let's analyze the moving averages for these stocks in the year 2008.

In [26]:
plt.figure(figsize=(12,4))
BAC['Close'].loc['2008'].rolling(window=30).mean().plot(label='30 days moving average')
BAC['Close'].loc['2008'].plot(label='BAC Close')
plt.legend()
Out[26]:
<matplotlib.legend.Legend at 0x14c123604f0>

Using .ta_plot(study='sma') to create a Simple Moving Averages plot of Morgan Stanley for the year 2015.

In [32]:
MS['Close'].loc['2015'].ta_plot(study='sma', periods=[13,21,55])

Using .ta_plot(study='boll') to create a Bollinger Band Plot for Bank of America for the year 2015.

In [33]:
BAC['Close'].loc['2015'].ta_plot(study='boll')
